This article is about the tribute paid to former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid by President Joe Biden. President Biden praised Reid's accomplishments and highlighted his dedication to serving the American people. As a mark of respect for Reid's memory, President Biden ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels, until sunset on the day of his interment. The order also extended to US embassies, consular offices, and other facilities abroad. The article concludes with President Biden's signature and the date.